Carter
</taxonomicName>
, the pronotal shape and the aedeagus being the main diagnostic features distinguishing the two species. See comments under 
<taxonomicName authority="Carter" authorityName="Carter" box="[1039,1328,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septemplagiata">
<emphasis box="[1039,1249,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. septemplagiata</emphasis>
Carter
</taxonomicName>
for other differences.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,151,1039]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,908,932]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the late E. B. Britton who facilitated my visit to the museums in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,254,943,967]" name="Australia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Australia</collectingCountry>
